Task 27-93-00-810-901-A

REV

Failure of ELAC2  <  - (20170801)

Effective on: 001-999
NOTE:   
If the fault appears at electrical power up, do first the TSM task 27-93-00-810-964 (ELAC Fault at Electrical Power Up) for:
•

ELACs L91/ L93/ L94 (PN 3945129101/ PN 3945129103/ PN 3945129104) or

•

ELAC L92 (PN 3945128208) or

•

ELAC L93 (PN 3945128209) or

•

ELAC L94 (PN 3945128210).

REV  < 
Possible Causes

  • ELAC-2 2CE2

  • wiring of the RLY ELAC FAULT signal from the relay to ELAC2

  • FCDC-1 3CE1

  • wiring from the pushbutton switch (6CE2) pin A/C3 to the first terminal block

  • P/BSW-FLT CTL/ELAC 2 6CE2

  • wiring of the DSI 39 signal at pin AA/12J (COM part) and pin AD/15E (MON part)

  • wirings of the DSI 39 and 47 signals

  • wirings of the DSI 20, 39 and 47 signals

    2. Job Set-up Information

    3. Fault Confirmation

    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 27-93-00-860-102 -A0 - (20130501)

    A. Side Stick Identification
    (1) Do the identification of the side stick installed on the aircraft SEE AMM 27-92-41-860-801 .

    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 27-93-00-860-083 -A0 - (20130201)

    B. Job Set-Up
    (1) Energize the aircraft electrical circuits SEE AMM 24-41-00-861-002 .
    (2) Make sure that the hydraulic systems are depressurized.
    (3) On the overhead panel 24VU:
    •

    release the FLT CTL/ELAC 2 pushbutton switch (the OFF legend of the FLT CTL/ELAC 2 pushbutton switch comes on).

    (4) On the overhead panel 24VU:
    •

    push the FLT CTL/ELAC 2 pushbutton switch (the OFF legend of the FLT CTL/ELAC 2 pushbutton switch goes off).

    NOTE:   
    In case of a reset of the ELAC2 with the circuit breaker, the supply breaking must be more than 5 seconds.
    NOTE:   
    If the ELAC FAULT warning disappears after several resets, replace the computer.

    Effective on: 001-999

    SUBTASK 27-93-00-740-176 -A0 - (20130201)

    C. Test
    (1) Do the BITE test of the EFCS (ground scanning) SEE AMM 27-96-00-740-001 .
    NOTE:   
    If the ground scanning does not give the maintenance message ELAC2, do the trouble shooting procedure
    27-93-00-810-947-A .

    4. Fault Isolation

    REV
    Effective on: 001-027, 783-800, 850-862

    Effective When SB 27-1243, is PRE on: 001-027, 783-799, 850-862
    Effective When SB 27-1251, is PRE on: 001-027, 783-799, 850-862
    Effective When SB 27-1263, is PRE on: 001-027, 783-799, 850-862
    Effective When SB 27-1265, is PRE on: 001-027, 783-799, 850-862
     < 

    SUBTASK 27-93-00-810-292 -J0 - (20170801)

    A.
    If the test confirms the fault:
    •

    Do the operational test of the ELACs SEE
    AMM 27-93-00-710-001
    to make sure that ELAC2 operates its associated surfaces.

    (1)
    If the flight controls move according to the ELAC2 servoing:
    (a)
    Remove ELAC1 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-000-001
    .
    (b)
    At ELAC2 receptacle, do a check of the resistance between pin AB/11J and pin AE/14C SEE
    ASM 27-92-03
    .
    1
    If the resistance is less than 280 ohms:
    a
    Remove the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .
    b
    Do a check of the resistance of the relay between pin X1 and pin X2 SEE
    ASM 27-92-03
    .
    •

    If the resistance is less than 280 ohms:

    . Replace the
    RELAY-ELAC 2 ANN SPLY (
    40CE2)  
    SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    . Install a new
    ELAC-2 (
    2CE2)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    •

    If the resistance is between 280 and 400 ohms:

    . Do a check and repair the
    wiring of the RLY ELAC FAULT signal from the relay to ELAC2 
    SEE
    ASM 27-92-03
    .

    . Install the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    . Install a new
    ELAC-2 (
    2CE2)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    2
    If the resistance is more than 400 ohms:
    a
    Remove the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .
    b
    Do a check of the resistance of the relay between pins X1 and X2 SEE
    ASM 27-92-03
    .
    •

    If the resistance is more than 400 ohms:

    . Replace the
    RELAY-ELAC 2 ANN SPLY (
    40CE2)  
    SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    . Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    •

    If the resistance is between 280 and 400 ohms:

    . Do a check and repair the
    wiring of the RLY ELAC FAULT signal from the relay to ELAC2 
    SEE
    ASM 27-92-03
    .

    . Install the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    . Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    3
    If the resistance is between 280 and 400 ohms:
    a
    Remove FCDC1 SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-000-001
    .
    •

    If the warning ELAC2 stays in view:

    . Install FCDC1 SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-400-001
    .

    . Continue the trouble shooting at Para. b_.

    •

    If the warning ELAC2 goes out of view, replace
    FCDC-1 (
    3CE1)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-000-001
    and SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-400-001
    .

    •

    Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    b
    Remove FCDC2 SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-000-001
    .
    •

    If the warning ELAC2 stays in view:

    . Install FCDC2 SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-400-001
    .

    . Continue the trouble shooting at Para. c_.

    •

    If the warning ELAC2 goes out of view, replace
    FCDC-2 (
    3CE2)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-000-001
    and SEE
    AMM 27-95-34-400-001
    .

    •

    Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    c
    Remove the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .
    •

    If the warning ELAC2 stays in view:

    . Install the relay (40CE2) SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    . Continue the trouble shooting at Para. d_.

    •

    If the warning ELAC2 goes out of view, replace the
    RELAY-ELAC 2 ANN SPLY (
    40CE2)  
    SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-03
    .

    •

    Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    d
    Do a check and repair the
    wiring of the DSI 4/2 (ELAC2 FAILED) signals 
    from FCDC1 (3CE1) and FCDC2 (3CE2) to the relay (40CE2) SEE
    ASM 27-95-04
    and SEE
    ASM 27-95-05
    .
    e
    Install ELAC2 SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .
    (2)
    If the flight controls do not move according to the ELAC2 servoing:
    (a)
    Replace
    ELAC-2 (
    2CE2)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-000-001
    and SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .
    (b)
    If the fault continues:
    1
    Do a check of the P/N of the FCDC installed on the aircraft:
    a
    If the P/N of the FCDC is 115370-0105 or 115370-0106 or 115370-1016 or 115370-1216:
    •

    Replace
    ELAC-1 (
    2CE1)  
    SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-000-001
    and SEE
    AMM 27-93-34-400-001
    .

    b
    If the P/N of the FCDC is different from 115370-0105 or 115370-0106 or 115370-1016 or 115370-1216:
    •

    Continue the trouble shooting at paragraph 4.A.(2)(c).

    (c)
    Do the trouble shooting procedure
    Effective on: 001-027, 783-800, 850-862 31-32-00-810-932-A
    related to the DSO 06 discrete output signal of ELAC2 SEE
    ASM 27-92-49
    .

    Do the trouble shooting procedure
    Effective on: 001-027, 783-800, 850-862 31-32-00-810-934-A
    related to the DGO 01 digital output signal of ELAC2 SEE
    ASM 27-92-52
    .

    (d)
    If the fault continues:
    1
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DGO 04 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part (DGI 01) and the MON part (DGO 04) to the COM part (DGI 01) SEE
    ASM 27-92-52
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    2
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DGI 04 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) MON part to the COM part SEE
    ASM 27-92-52
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    3
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DGI 05 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) MON part to the COM part SEE
    ASM 27-92-52
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    4
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSO 06 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part (DSI 48) and the MON part (DSO 06) to the COM part (DSI 48) SEE
    ASM 27-92-49
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    5
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSI 07 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part SEE
    ASM 27-92-44
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    6
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSI 10 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part SEE
    ASM 27-92-44
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    7
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSI 13 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part SEE
    ASM 27-92-44
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    8
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSI 17 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part to the MON part SEE
    ASM 27-92-44
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    9
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the DSI 20 signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part and the MON part to the ground terminal SEE
    ASM 27-92-40
    .
    •

    If the wiring is not correct, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If the wiring is correct, continue the procedure.

    10
    Replace the (
    4CE1)  
    and (
    4CE2)  
    or the
    SSU-CAPT (100CE1) 
    and
    SSU-F/O (100CE2) 
    (if a new-generation side-stick unit is installed on the aircraft) SEE
    AMM 27-92-41-000-002
    and SEE
    AMM 27-92-41-400-002
    or SEE
    AMM 27-92-41-000-802
    and SEE
    AMM 27-92-41-400-802
    .
    (e)
    If the fault continues:
    1
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the PWR SPLY + 28VDC signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part and the MON part to the first terminal block SEE
    ASM 27-92-02
    .
    •

    If there is no continuity, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If there is continuity, continue the procedure.

    2
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the PWR SPLY GND signal 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part and the MON part to the ground terminal SEE
    ASM 27-92-02
    .
    •

    If there is no continuity, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If there is continuity, continue the procedure.

    3
    Do a check of the
    wiring of the CTL + 28VDC and ELAC2 ENGAGED (DSI 50) signals 
    from the ELAC2 (2CE2) COM part and the MON part to the pushbutton switch (6CE2) SEE
    ASM 27-92-02
    .
    •

    If there is no continuity, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If there is continuity, continue the procedure.

    4
    Do a check of the
    wiring from the pushbutton switch (6CE2) pin A/C3 to the first terminal block 
    SEE
    ASM 27-92-02
    .
    •

    If there is no continuity, repair the above wiring.

    •

    If there is continuity, continue the procedure.

    5
    Replace the
    P/BSW-FLT CTL/ELAC 2 (
    6CE2)  
    SEE
    AIPC 27-92-08-02
    .
